companyProfile.companyDescription: Britannia Industries Limited is an India-based food products company. The Company is primarily engaged in the manufacturing and sale of various food products. The Company's product categories include biscuits, dairy, breads, rusk, cakes, nutrition bar, and snacking. Its biscuit products include Good Day, Marie Gold, NutriChoice, Milk Bikis, Tiger, 50-50, Jim Jam, Treat, Little Hearts, Pure Magic, Nice Time and Biscafe. The Company's dairy products include cheese, Winkin' Cow, Come Alive Paneer, Come Alive Dahi, ghee and Dairy Whitener. Its bread products include gourmet breads, white bread and wheat flour breads. Its gourmet breads include Fruit Bun, fruit bread, Choco bread and Choco Bun. Its white breads include Healthy Slice Bread, Sweet Bread, Vitarich Bread and Sandwich Bread. Its cake products include Gobbles, Fudge, Muffils, Nuts and Raisin Romance Cake, Roll Yo! and Tiffin Fun. Its snacking products include Treat Croissant, Treat Creme Wafers and Time Pass Salted Snacks.

recentNews.headline: Britannia may name new CEO in 3-4 months, MD Varun Berry gets additional charge
recentNews.intro: Britannia Industries plans to appoint a new CEO following Rajneet Kohli's departure. Varun Berry has been designated as interim CEO effective 8 May
recentNews.imagecaption: Varun Berryhas been designated as CEO of Britannia by the board of directors, Pic by Hemant Mishra/Mint

recentNews.headline: Escalating India-Pakistan tensions trigger stockpiling in border regions
recentNews.intro: Union food and consumer affairs minister Pralhad Joshi urged the public to disregard what he called misleading messages about food stocks, adding that there are enough supplies available in the country.
recentNews.imagecaption: Packaged food companies said demand has increased from border cities in north India. Companies assured supplies of adequate stock in such markets.

recentNews.intro: Stocks to watch: L&T, Titan Company, Coal India, Lupin, Suzlon Energy, are among the stocks to watch in today's trading session.

recentNews.imagecaption: Q4 results today: Britannia Industries will declare earnings today.

recentNews.headline: Britannia, Tata Consumer to HUL: 14 Nifty FMCG stocks rally up to 30% from March lows. What's behind the surge?
recentNews.intro: FMCG stocks have rallied in April, driven by positive investor sentiment and government measures boosting consumption. Analysts anticipate a strong recovery in earnings growth in FY26, with valuations now reasonable after previous selling pressure in the sector.
recentNews.imagecaption: 14 Nifty FMCG stocks rally up to 30% from March lows: Tata Consumer, GCPL top gainers

recentNews.intro: Stocks to Buy: Britannia Industries , Aarti Industries are 2 technical picks recommended by Reliance Securities for 14-26% upside with investment horizon of 8-10 week. Check details
recentNews.imagecaption: Stocks to Buy: 2 technical picks by Reliance Sec

recentNews.headline: Nifty 50 valuation to rise after inclusion of Zomato, Jio Financial Services shares
recentNews.intro: Nifty 50 P/E ratio stands at 19.9x, based on an estimated EPS of  ?1,186 for FY26. However, post the rebalancing, the index is projected to trade at a P/E of 20.2x, with a revised EPS estimate of  ?1,171 for the same period.
recentNews.imagecaption: Zomato and Jio Financial Services shares will replace BPCL and Britannia Industries shares in Nifty 50.

recentNews.headline: Britannia's Rajneet Kohli joins Hindustan Unilever as executive director
recentNews.intro: Kohli, former CEO of Britannia Industries, will lead Hindustan Unilever's food and refreshment division, its second-largest business unit.
recentNews.imagecaption: In 2023-24, the foods and refreshment business contributed 25% of HUL?s turnover. (Reuters)

recentNews.headline: Nifty 50 Rejig: Zomato, Jio Financial Services to replace BPCL, Britannia Industries in frontline index
recentNews.intro: Nifty 50 Rejig: Zomato, Jio Financial Services, PowerGrid Corporation of India and CG Power and Industrial Solutions are expected to see the highest passive inflows in the Nifty indices March rebalancing.
recentNews.imagecaption: Nifty 50 Rejig: Zomato shares inclusion into the frontline Nifty 50 index is expected to lead to passive inflows worth $602 million in the stock
